[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T19:08:43+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A Raptor Lake chip, atop its blue box.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4ntahvRpLuFwDWEN9Z1-ohahf7M=/18x0:2640x1748/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73632944/intelcorei9_11900K_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Tom Warren / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"v9kKIf\">Intel may have one less worry on <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/1/24210656/intel-is-laying-off-over-10000-employees-and-will-cut-10-billion-in-costs\">its very full plate</a>: it believes it has now fully addressed its desktop CPU instability woes with 13th and 14th Gen \u201cRaptor Lake\u201d chips. </p>\n<p id=\"afh1uE\">While the company says there\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206529/intel-13th-14th-gen-crashing-instability-cpu-voltage-q-a\">still no fix</a> for processors that are already damaged, it confirms to me that the \u201cVmin Shift Instability\u201d is <em><strong>the </strong></em>root cause of the unusual instability and crashes ", "id": 1269922, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262287/intel-13th-14th-gen-crash-raptor-lake-root-cause-fix", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Intel says its Raptor Lake crashing chip nightmare is over", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T17:33:21+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the WordPress logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zMD36VxriYMcQhvrLlQ1tG03fAY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73632750/STK302_WORDPRESS.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>WordPress and its cofounder Matt Mullenweg are embroiled in a public battle against the third-party hosting provider WP Engine.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262410/wordpress-fight-trademarks-open-source-mullenweg\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1269187, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262410/wordpress-fight-trademarks-open-source-mullenweg", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The latest on the WordPress fight over trademarks and open source", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T16:30:32+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing Marques Brownlee holding up a phone with the Panels app open\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hv1S8Xum4QEz5VYdTE-Ash-NAdE=/182x0:2234x1368/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73632643/panels_app_update.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: MKBHD <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MRtg6A1f2Ko\" target=\"_blank\">via YouTube</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"h3a0HU\">MKBHD\u2019s new wallpaper app has received its first big update after <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/24/24253023/mkbhd-panels-wallpaper-app-response-criticism\">users criticized the app over pricing</a> and the advertising setup for free accounts. On Friday, the <a href=\"https://x.com/panels_art/status/1842227074284536287?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1842227074284536287%7Ctwgr%5E%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&amp;ref_url=about%3Asrcdoc\">Panels account announced</a> on X that people using the app for free can now downl", "id": 1268946, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262350/mkbhd-panels-wallpaper-app-fewer-ads-update", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "MKBHD\u2019s wallpaper app updated with fewer ads", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T15:45:43+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"One dollar bill photoshopped to have the Dish, DirecTV, and AOL Time Warner logos on it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Y5G_geOjH5FpL51TZkEx0kYq0H8=/275x274:1713x1233/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73632542/247300_ONE_DOLLAR_MERGER_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jkvZn9\">This week, DirecTV <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/30/24258196/directv-dish-merger-tpg-deal-announcement\">announced it intends to buy Dish, Sling TV,</a> and the rest of EchoStar\u2019s television business for a dollar (while also taking on all of Dish\u2019s debt), combining almost 20 million satellite TV subscribers from two companies that have been circling one another for decades.</p>\n<p id=\"uibRD3\">But it\u2019s not just DirecTV and Dish.  AT&amp;T, Comcast, Verizon, General Electric, GM, News Corp, Tumblr, and the various incarnations of Time Warner have also gotten mixed up or spl", "id": 1268627, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24259360/directv-dish-merger-timeline-aol-timewarner", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "From AOL Time Warner to DirecTV and Dish: 20 years of media mergers", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T14:25:33+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing Matt Mullenweg at WordCamp\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/eP1oZvxx0QUcuwnNH3gekkuVwpI=/160x0:2065x1270/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73632344/mullenweg_eu_wordcamp.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Matt Mullenweg at WordCamp 2024 in Europe.</em> | Image: WordCamp</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The lines between the WordPress open-source project, the nonprofit backing it, and the commercial arm owned by Automattic are blurring.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262232/matt-mullenweg-wordpress-org-wp-engine\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1268389, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262232/matt-mullenweg-wordpress-org-wp-engine", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Matt Mullenweg: \u2018WordPress.org\u00a0just belongs to me\u2019", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T13:54:53+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Arc logo on pink and blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/py8hFArIQM160c_UB8tkdEaV9Cs=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73632264/STK283_ARC_BROWSER_D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"uKiSzw\">After months of waiting, now Android users can take the Arc Search app for a spin. It\u2019s now <a href=\"https://play.google.com/apps/testing/company.thebrowser.arc\">available as an open beta</a> on the Google Play Store after developers teased <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/23/24226870/arc-is-coming-to-android-soon\">an Android version</a> of the app in August.</p>\n<p id=\"PAAht9\">Arc is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23462235/arc-web-browser-review\">The Browser Company\u2019s take on web browsing</a>, billing itself as offering better customization options than competitors. The Arc Search app also comes with an AI feature, called \u201cBrowse ", "id": 1268390, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262056/arc-search-android-beta-mobile-web-browser", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Arc\u2019s \u2018better mobile browser\u2019 is now available on Android", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T13:51:09+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of a person using a smartphone-like device near water.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TW6uWGdaeO7F8qoXWwI3SXRheNI=/125x0:1475x900/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73632246/Boox_Palma_lead.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The 6.1-inch Boox Palma looks a lot like a smartphone, but it\u2019s designed to be an e-reader. </em> | Image: Boox</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"O2wu5X\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22745670/amazon-kindle-paperwhite-2021-review-usb-c-signature-edition-display-e-reader-books\">Kindles</a> are great and all, but if you want a pocketable e-reader that doesn\u2019t require you lock yourself into Amazon\u2019s ecosystem the <strong>Boox Palma</strong> might be worth a look. The 6.1-inch ebook reader normally runs for $279.99, but now through October 9th readers of<em> The Verge </em>can score an rare $30 discount and a free cover case (valued at $16) when they buy it from <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.c", "id": 1268064, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262072/boox-palma-e-reader-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The smartphone-sized\u00a0Boox\u00a0Palma\u00a0e-reader\u2019s on sale exclusively for\u00a0Verge\u00a0readers      ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T13:42:56+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Oura Ring Gen 3 sitting in a jewelry tray with other rings.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Q56bgrDSL4o8MOPp7P04WZn7pWg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73632223/vsong_211117_4890_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The fashionable and discreet Oura Ring Generation 3&nbsp;is down to nearly its best price to date.</em> | Photo by Victoria Song / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Goa070\">Oura may have just announced the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/3/24260260/oura-ring-4-price-specs-smart-ring-wearable\">new Oura Ring 4</a>, but until its release on October 15th, the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22789248/oura-ring-3-review-sleep-tracker-fitness-tracker\"><strong>Oura Ring Generation 3</strong></a> is still <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/1/24259284/oura-ring-samsung-galaxy-ring-ultrahuman-ring-air-ringconn-circular-ring-evie-ring-review-wearables\">the best smart ring on", "id": 1268065, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24261151/oura-ring-generation-3-amazon-fire-tv-cube-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The\u00a0Oura Ring Gen 3, our favorite smart ring,\u00a0is nearly matching its best price to date  ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T11:45:18+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Roblox logo illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nkwoJcA2XM4ECJOvQk22AN5q6Ck=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73631950/STK146_Roblox_New.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"tYopnR\">A popular financial newsletter is accusing Roblox of allowing large-scale child sexual exploitation and inappropriate content on its platform, drawing on years of media reports. The allegations are <a href=\"https://thebearcave.substack.com/p/problems-at-roblox-rblx-4\">detailed in <em>The Bear Cave</em></a>, a short selling newsletter \u2014 but Roblox says <em>The Bear Cave\u2019s</em> founder is highlighting rare instances of abuse to profit by making the service look bad.</p>\n<p id=\"gZlJ8F\">\u201cThis article contains misleading, irresponsible and in many cases false accusations about Roblox to further the author\u2019s motives as a short seller,\u201d Eric Porterfield, Roblox\u2019s senior director o", "id": 1267600, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262033/roblox-the-bear-cave-child-abuse", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Financial newsletter accuses Roblox of enabling child abuse", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T11:36:19+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Samsung Galaxy S10 Plus\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/q0r-mNlmD4BDlOIRaBVjZ2swtPU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73631928/galaxys10_vladsavov.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vlad Savov / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"RmFiO8\">A Samsung smart home software update released this week put some users\u2019 Galaxy S10 and Note 10 (including e, Lite, Plus, and 5G versions) and A90 and M51 smartphones in an infinite boot loop, rendering their devices useless. After some sleuthing, <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/samsunggalaxy/s/5J1Z32OIR4\">Reddit users</a> narrowed it down to a Samsung SmartThings framework app update that was automatically applied to the devices.</p>\n<p id=\"SLCITW\">According to posts on Reddit, Samsung <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/samsunggalaxy/comments/1fv2qyz/samsung_koreas_initial_statement_posted_in/\">replaced the buggy update</a> with a new version that won\u2019t brick the ", "id": 1267601, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24261940/samsung-smart-home-smartthings-bug-bootloop-galaxy-s10-note-10", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A buggy Samsung smart home update broke old Galaxy S10 phones, but there\u2019s a fix", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T11:30:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Facebook logo on a blue background, surrounded by dark blue circles of various sizes\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bcfcvaY-ma4F1pCymNI9gBAimf4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73631902/STK040_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_2_facebook.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bKzdIq\">Facebook is announcing a host of updates to its platform today, many of which focus on pushing users outside of their social bubble of friends and family.</p>\n<p id=\"WWykLA\">Among the updates are new tabs being added to Facebook that are meant to surface more content for users, including recommendations based on a person\u2019s location. A new \u201cLocal\u201d tab will collect content from other Facebook surfaces like the resale platform Marketplace, local groups, and events \u2014 essentially what sounds like Facebook\u2019s version of Nextdoor. The Local tab is being tested in 10 US cities includi", "id": 1267602, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24261170/facebook-recommendations-explore-local-tab-tiktok", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Facebook is going to show you even more content from accounts you don\u2019t follow", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T10:46:31+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An AI-generated still from a video of a child running on the beach with a kite.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1mK9bZiPmNNIav6m5HEmPdyn4XM=/0x1:2004x1337/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73631784/ai_label__1_.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Meta</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"eSwhin\">A new AI-powered video generator from Meta produces high-definition footage complete with sound, <a href=\"https://ai.meta.com/research/movie-gen/\">the company announced today</a>. The announcement comes several months after competitor <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/15/24074151/openai-sora-text-to-video-ai\">OpenAI unveiled Sora</a>, its text-to-video model \u2014 though public access to Movie Gen isn\u2019t happening yet.</p>\n<p id=\"3IdZe2\">Movie Gen uses text inputs to automatically generate new videos, as well as edit existing footage or still images. <em>The New York Times </em><a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/10/04/technology/me", "id": 1266498, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24261990/meta-movie-gen-ai-video-generator-openai-sora", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Meta announces Movie Gen, an AI-powered video generator", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of a Clue game made inside of Fortnite.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/i01plZOPYeiJw4lrqJas6o9Fkig=/0x0:2391x1594/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73631635/GirlLobby.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Hasbro</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"okjL6x\">Epic is trying to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/7/23990660/lego-fortnite-release-epic\">turn<em> Fortnite </em>into an ecosystem of games</a> and has enticed the likes of Lego to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/27/24084644/fortnite-new-lego-games-raft-survival-obby-fun\">build experiences for the platform</a>. Now, Hasbro is jumping in as well, with plans to create <em>Fortnite</em> adaptations of its most popular board games.</p>\n<p id=\"pWu6Ws\">The first is called <em>Murder Mystery: Clue</em>, and it\u2019s available today. It\u2019s not exactly a board game (see the screenshot above) but, rather, a reimagining in the form of a multiplayer murder myster", "id": 1266499, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24261095/hasbro-board-games-fortnite", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Hasbro is bringing classic board games to Fortnite, starting with Clue", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-04T09:43:39+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of a computer with a smiling face, on a Vergecast background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/A-cwYTW1nIi1k2H7Kcntw2StOvg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73631607/VST_1004_Site.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cm4agR\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/1/24259187/microsoft-copilot-redesign-vision-voice-features-inflection-ai\">new Microsoft Copilot</a> is a big departure. It shed some of its Bing-y styling and increasingly corporate vibes in favor of something warmer and friendlier, all in an effort to be more than just a work tool. It might just be a website redesign, but it feels like a shift in <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/1/24259209/microsoft-ai-ceo-must